    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-09T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-09T09:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/2139: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-09T22:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 9, 1937—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 9—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1127. Hankow’s December 2, 11 a.m.,<note n="36" xml:id="d486fn36">Not
                        printed.</note> regarding party leaving Hankow for Canton December
                        10th.<note n="37" xml:id="d486fn37">This party reached Hong Kong at 9 p.m.,
                        December 13.</note> Following reply received from Japanese Consul General:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I hasten to communicate to you in reply to your letters of December 2nd
                            and December 5th that necessary information about 70 foreigners of
                            various nationalities leaving Hankow by train for Hong Kong at 10 a.m.,
                            on December 10th were immediately transmitted to our naval and military
                            authorities and that necessary arrangements have already been made not
                            to attack from the Japanese side the special train with the foreign
                            party on board.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Hankow, repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
